<p>WIDE SHOT of entire scene.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>GUNSHIP<br />
Mark.</p>
</div>
<br />
ANGLE ON explosion at the center of the dig. Several CUTS TO<br />
Commandos cautiously straining to look at the aftermath. In<br />
the last of these, a Commando is suddenly grabbed by an<br />
enormous pseudopod and dragged offscreen.
<p>WIDE SHOT of explosion site, where we now seen a large<br />
amoeboid creature, shimmering with many colors, reaching out<br />
with multiple tentacles. Covering the mass, we see what look<br />
like smaller protrusions that are roughly shaped like human<br />
appendages, including heads, that only last for a moment<br />
before collapsing back into the mass and then regenerating,<br />
which happens continuously.</p>
<p>What follows is a firefight where more and more Commandos are<br />
pulled into the mass, with some deserting. At the climax, a<br />
very large appendage flings itself towards the command<br />
gunship.</p>
<p>CLOSE SHOT of Major Stanton</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>MAJOR STANTON<br />
Code Red, repeat, Code Red! Fire<br />
the-</p>
</div>
<p>EXT. COMMAND GUNSHIP</p>
<p>Appendage envelopes command gunship and begins pulling it<br />
into the central mass.</p>
<p>INT. TROOP TRANSPORT HELICOPTER</p>
<p>OVER SHOULDER shot of Dr. Jafari watching this attack, then<br />
REVERSE SHOT on Dr. Jafari and JACOBS in cockpit.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>JACOBS<br />
Fuck! Major called Code Red! We<br />
have to get out of here!</p>
<p>DR. JAFARI<br />
What's Code Red?</p>
<p>JACOBS<br />
We're blasting the site!</p>
<p>DR. JAFARI<br />
What? No! Why would they-</p>
<p>JACOBS<br />
It's gone, Doc, they're gone, and<br />
no guarantees for us!</p>
</div>
<p>EXT. TROOP TRANSPORT HELICOPTER</p>
<p>Helicopter starts to take off, but as it starts to turn away,<br />
we CUT TO:</p>
<p>EXT. COMMANDO POSITION</p>
<p>Two Commandos with a large backpack run towards the center of<br />
the dig. As a tentacle lunges for them, they trigger the<br />
backpack, an SADM explosive. As the explosion begins, CUT<br />
BACK TO:</p>
<p>EXT. TROOP TRANSPORT HELICOPTER</p>
<p>Where we see the explosion rapidly overtake the troop<br />
transport. Dr. Jafari bows his head and rocks back and forth.<br />
The explosion envelopes the transport. CUT BACK TO:</p>
<p>EXT. DIG SITE</p>
<p>WIDE SHOT of the site, where the explosion rises into the<br />
air. As the scene starts to fade out, we hear Captain Good in<br />
voiceover:</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>CAPTAIN GOOD (V.O.)<br />
(in Urdu) Until we meet again.</p>
</div>
<br />
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p>FADE TO BLACK.</p>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;">ACT 5</p>
<p>INT. SECURITY DESK SITE-76</p>
<p>This act opens with several shots and a voiceover by AGENT<br />
KLIKS, who is conversing with an unknown party on his phone.</p>
<p>Focus on Security Desk engaged in normal activity.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>KLIKS (V.O.)<br />
No, that was never the deal. The<br />
arrangements got fucked up somehow.</p>
</div>
<p>INT. SITE-76 ARCHIVES</p>
<p>Focus on that bored Librarian reading her book.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>KLIKS (V.O.)<br />
An information swap is nothing like<br />
allowing a containment breach.</p>
</div>
<p>INT. OUTSIDE CONTAINMENT CELL OF SCP-140</p>
<p>Focus on the cell door and its two Guards, standing at<br />
attention.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>KLIKS (V.O.)<br />
I never said that! (pause) Where<br />
are you getting your information?</p>
</div>
<p>INT. AGENT'S KLIKS' OFFICE SITE-76</p>
<p>The once ornate office is now nearly empty of lived-in<br />
furnishings. Instead, we see bare Foundation fixtures, and<br />
two large taped-up boxes on the floor. Next to these are two<br />
expensive-looking overnight bags.</p>
<p>Kliks is pacing the office, talking on a cheap cellphone that<br />
looks like a &quot;burner&quot;. He is wearing a summer scarf in the<br />
European style, as well as a hat. He looks ready to travel.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>KLIKS<br />
Of course I want access to the<br />
Library. The whole Foundation does.<br />
But your price is too high.<br />
(extended pause) I'll have to think<br />
about that. (extended pause) Yes,<br />
that sounds much better. But I have<br />
to leave you now. I'm on the move.<br />
(pause) To my new roost. Finally,<br />
I'm getting the respect I deserve.<br />
(pause) I'll be in touch. Ciao.</p>
</div>
<p>Kliks shuts off the phone, grins at it, then tosses it into a<br />
heavy duty shredder attached to a bare desk. He picks up the<br />
two overnight bags, and walks to the door. Looking around one<br />
more time, he smiles and leaves the office, whose lights shut<br />
off automatically when he leaves.</p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p>FADE TO:</p>
</div>
<p>INT. CORRIDOR LEADING TO SECURITY DESK-AFTERNOON</p>
<p>FRONT SHOT of GREY, DR. MAHTO, and 2 GUARD escorts, slowly<br />
walking to the Security Desk. Grey has his messenger bag, and<br />
each Guard is carrying a travel bag belonging to Dr. Mahto.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(furious) It was all a lie, Simon.<br />
This is nothing like what the<br />
Foundation said I would be doing.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
I don't know what to tell you.<br />
Today was extreme, but not<br />
unexpected. Your orientation-</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
43 people died today! That's not<br />
unexpected? That much daily death?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Look, Zeta-9 knew the score. Mobile<br />
Task Forces are our best, but that<br />
means they get the tough jobs.<br />
Sometimes they're impossible.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
How can you tolerate that, Simon?<br />
It's&#8230;it's monstrous. Unthinkable.</p>
</div>
<p>CLOSE SHOT on Dr. Mahto</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(sincere) I have always envisioned<br />
my research helping people, serving<br />
humanity. But now I realize I've<br />
signed on to just holding back<br />
cosmic monsters and keeping the<br />
body count to a minimum!</p>
</div>
<p>WIDEN SHOT to Group. Grey stops and turns to Dr. Mahto, then<br />
to the Guards.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>GREY<br />
Guards, give us a moment.</p>
</div>
<p>The Guards step to the side. FRONT SHOT on Grey and Dr. Mahto<br />
in PROFILE.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>GREY<br />
Doctor. (pause) Jagruti. Today,<br />
(pause) today you saw more than<br />
most new researchers see in 3<br />
years. It's awful on the best days.<br />
You just saw the worst. But that's<br />
it, you have to stop feeling sorry<br />
for yourself and get on with it.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(furious) How dare you, Simon! I am<br />
not feeling sorry for myself! The<br />
Foundation lied to me. I was<br />
tricked into making the wrong<br />
decision.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(thinking) I guess that old saying<br />
is right, then.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
What old saying?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
The truth hurts.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(exasperated) How does that even<br />
apply here, Simon?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
I don't know! (pause) I'm just&#8230;<br />
(long pause) You saw the truth,<br />
Doctor. More than most people ever<br />
will. And yeah, most people don't<br />
want the truth, because it hurts to<br />
know. (pause) But you're a<br />
scientist. I mean, I'm not one, but<br />
I thought that the truth was<br />
everything to scientists. When you<br />
do an experiment, or whatever, do<br />
you give up if it doesn't work the<br />
way you wanted?</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(disarmed) No, not if you are a<br />
good scientist. Sometimes, the<br />
failures provide the most<br />
information.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Then you're in the right place,<br />
Doctor. Lotta failure here.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
But how do I get past all the<br />
deception, Simon? How do I ever<br />
trust the Foundation again?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(beat) You don't. Ever. You just<br />
get used to it. You figure out how<br />
to contribute while maintaining<br />
whatever morals you think you have.<br />
Your first meeting with the Ethics<br />
Committee will clarify a lot.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(beat) And that's it?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(long pause) That's it.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
(long pause) I see. (beat, change<br />
in demeaner) Well, I do think that<br />
I trust YOU, Simon. Maybe that's<br />
enough for me to continue.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(stunned) I hope so, Jagruti.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
So back to your proposal. (beat) If<br />
I could figure out the mechanism<br />
for SCP-140 expansion, it would be<br />
more meaningful than anything I<br />
have worked on to date.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Yes, it would.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
140 seems able to convert a certain<br />
form of matter to retrocausal<br />
energy. If we could monitor local<br />
quantum entanglement during an<br />
expansion event-</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Doctor-</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
-we could measure the changes in<br />
entanglement correlation, and see<br />
how it applies to the local quantum<br />
field! Then-</p>
<p>GREY<br />
DOCTOR. I. Have. No. Idea what<br />
you're talking about. (beat) But<br />
it's good you do. Let's get to Site<br />
19. Look up Dr. Xyanks when you get<br />
there. (to Guards) Guards, we're<br />
ready.</p>
</div>
<p>REVERSE SHOT as Grey, Mahto, and Guard walk away, continuing<br />
towards the Security Desk. Mahto continues to formulate,<br />
while Grey just nods.</p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p>CUT TO:</p>
</div>
<p>INT. SECURITY DESK SITE-76</p>
<p>ANGLE ON Grey and Mahto as they come up behind main desk and<br />
stop short. Camera continues forward to reveal a large<br />
contingent of Guards, researchers, and staff milling about<br />
and talking to each other. CMDR YOO and LT. QUINN seem to be<br />
a particular focus of attention, while Agent Kliks stand near<br />
the desk, observing the proceedings. The mood is festive.<br />
Cmdr Yoo's left forearm has a cast with many signatures and<br />
doodles.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>GREY<br />
Geezus, did we miss something?</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
In fact, you missed several<br />
somethings.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
Oh, I'm sorry we missed it! Some<br />
good news is welcome.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
What? What happened?</p>
</div>
<p>ANGLE ON Cmdr Yoo and Lt. Quinn approaching.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>KLIKS<br />
Special Agent, you are now speaking<br />
to Captain Jesse Quinn. Show some<br />
respect.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Wow, that's great news, ah,<br />
Captain.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
Jesse, I am so proud of you. I wish<br />
we had more time to work together.</p>
<p>CAPTAIN QUINN<br />
Thanks, Doctor. But I can tell,<br />
you're needed at Site-19. I'll hold<br />
down the fort here.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Hold down the&#8212;</p>
<p>CMDR YOO<br />
Captain Quinn is the new Chief of<br />
Security for 76. (to Quinn, in<br />
jest) Don't botch this, Jess. I'll<br />
have lots of eyes watching you.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(realizing) OK, catching up slowly.<br />
Does that mean (smiles all about)<br />
Commander, are you moving to Site<br />
19? Yoon-hee, that's incredible!<br />
(calmer) I mean, Commander.</p>
<p>CMDR YOO<br />
Yes, Agent Grey. As long as they<br />
keep telling me it doesn't have to<br />
be a desk job, I'll keep saying<br />
yes. Plus, who's going to keep you<br />
and Kliks from driving each other<br />
to drink?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(sickly) Oh, no, no really?</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
The powers that be have come to<br />
their senses, and are moving me to<br />
my rightful domain. I've been given<br />
an &quot;at large&quot; portfolio: dabbling<br />
in whatever I deem most important<br />
across the entire grid. Don't<br />
worry, Grey, I'll give you a taste<br />
now and then.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(looking at the group) Well, two<br />
out of three isn't bad.</p>
<p>CMDR YOO<br />
If it's any consolation, Agent, we<br />
get to take the jet back.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Nice perk, Commander. Well, then, I<br />
guess we're ready. Guard, please<br />
arrange an escort and take<br />
everyone's luggage.</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
Simon, I want to say goodbye to a<br />
few people here. It will just take<br />
a moment.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
I think the jet has to wait for us.</p>
</div>
<p>Dr. Mahto steps into the crowd. Kliks moves closer to Grey<br />
and they have a quiet conversation.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>KLIKS<br />
A quick chat, not in front of the<br />
others.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Well, Yoon-hee must know.</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
No, the Commander has no official<br />
knowledge. Remember that.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(beat) Sure. So you have some new<br />
insult you want to spring on me?</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
In good time. But right now, I need<br />
to apologize. Something did go<br />
wrong with 140.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
Christ, Kliks, you think? A Top 20<br />
Keter breached! What possible-</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
It has to do with&#8230;our project.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(silent, then) Like I said. How?</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
Let's say that we may have an 'in'<br />
now with someone who knows&#8230;a Way.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(pause) I don't know, Kliks. We've<br />
been lied to again and again. Seems<br />
like you're moving too fast. And I<br />
don't have any control.</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
With us both at Site-19 it will be<br />
easier to coordinate. And for you<br />
to be more informed.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(distressed) So this may have all<br />
been worth it. All these deaths.<br />
What the hell's wrong with me?</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
The Foundation does it to us all.<br />
Might as well put it to the best<br />
possible use.</p>
</div>
<p>Dr. Mahto approaches with Cmdr Yoo and 3 Guard escorts. Also<br />
entering the scene is the PILOT taking our crew to Site-19.<br />
(S)he is a less armored guard, wearing a visored helmet<br />
obscuring his/er eyes. (S)he also wears gloves&#8230;similar to<br />
the Sarkite (recall none of our main cast saw this). PAN IN<br />
on the gloves. Then CUT TO WIDE SHOT on Dr. Mahto.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
All right, Simon, I'm ready.</p>
<p>CMDR YOO<br />
Do you know your first assignment,<br />
Jagruti?</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
I am part of Dr. Gears' research<br />
group. I don't know much more than<br />
that right now.</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(knowingly) Oh, man, Gears!</p>
<p>DR. MAHTO<br />
What does THAT mean?</p>
<p>GREY<br />
(pause) I can tell you some stories<br />
on the plane.</p>
<p>KLIKS<br />
(acknowledging Pilot) Pilot, we're<br />
ready to depart. Off to the<br />
mothership, everyone!</p>
</div>
<p>Grey suddenly looks distracted, and is looking at the Pilot.<br />
The group begins to depart. Grey turns to Dr. Mahto.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>GREY<br />
(distracted) Oh, almost forgot.<br />
Never had a chance this morning.</p>
</div>
<p>Grey steps back and formally extends a hand to Dr. Mahto.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>GREY<br />
(ambivalent, serious) Welcome to<br />
the Foundation, Doctor.</p>
</div>
<p>Dr. Mahto shakes Grey's hand once. The group turns towards a<br />
corridor and heads towards it. Grey taps Kliks on the<br />
shoulder and says something unheard. Both briefly stop, look<br />
at the Pilot, then continue walking. SHOT PULLS BACK to show<br />
the entire hall as the group departs. SHOT DISSOLVES up to<br />
the weigh station bay, then WIDENS to show the whole weigh<br />
station. Continues to PULL BACK to show a construction dig<br />
next to the weigh station hidden from the highway. Across the<br />
screen we see the text &quot;Solaris Construction &amp; Planning.&quot; We<br />
hover over this scene as the text and scene begin to fade,<br />
apart from the leading letters &quot;S-C-P&quot;, as we&#8230;</p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p>CUT TO BLACK</p>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;">THE END</p>

